Actor Rapulana Seiphumo, who has played the role of Tau in Generations for several years, is now joining Mzansi Magic's The Queen. He will be reunited with his former onscreen wife Connie Ferguson, who plays Harriet in the soapie. In the soapie, the seasoned actor will play Hector Sebata. Nomsa Philiso, who is the director of M-Net Local Entertainment Channels, expressed her excitement about the star's move to the channel. “Mzansi Magic’s The Queen continues to entertain viewers with its star-studded cast and unpredictable plots and twists. Packed with suspense and drama, this is local storytelling at its best,” she said in a statement.  